SECTION 1. Chapter 30 of the Private Acts of 1975, as amended by Chapter 39 of the
Private Acts of 1989, and any other acts amendatory thereto, is amended in Chapter IX by
deleting SECTION 2 and substituting:
SECTION 2. For the purpose of providing an efficient system of roads, highways, and
bridges and the building, construction, reconstruction, maintenance, and repair of roads,
highways, and bridges in Bedford County, Tennessee, the office of County Road
Superintendent is hereby created. The County Road Superintendent shall be deemed to be the
chief administrative officer of the highway department, which builds and maintains the roads of
the county in accordance with the Tennessee County Uniform Highway Law, codified at
Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 54, Chapter 7, Parts 1 and 2, as amended from time to time.
The County Road Superintendent in office on the effective date of this act shall continue
to serve until the expiration of his term. At the August election in 2028, and every four (4) years
thereafter, the County Road Superintendent shall be elected by a majority of the qualified voters
of Bedford County. The superintendent shall receive a salary as provided in general law.
The superintendent shall be a person of skill and experience in highway or bridge
construction work, having not less than five (5) years full-time experience and employment while
engaged in such work, and shall be a person of good moral character. Any candidate for the
office of superintendent shall be qualified as provided in general law.
SECTION 3. All provisions of Chapter 30 of the Private Acts of 1975, as amended by
Chapter 39 of the Private Acts of 1989, and any other acts amendatory thereto, in conflict
